		<p>Sanger used these notes for a speech given at the <org>Berkshire Hotel</org> in
				<place>Reading, PA</place> on Dec 3, 1920. For a typed draft see S70:856. Note
			handwritten by Sanger at top of first page reads:"1919--deaths 302 under 1 year--
				<lb/><supplied resp="MSPP">"1919--deaths</supplied> 154 still born.</p>
